Implemented the minimal fix in:

- `clap_builder/src/parser/parser.rs`

Change made:
- `did_you_mean_error` no longer mutates the `ArgMatcher` to mark a suggested argument as command-line provided when `ignore_errors(true)` is enabled.
- This prevents ignored “did you mean” errors like `--ig` from blocking default insertion for `--ignore-immutable`.

Verification run:
- `cargo test -p clap_builder --lib parser:: --quiet`
- Reproduced the reported case with a temporary local project depending on this checkout; both assertions now pass.
- `cargo fmt --all --check` passed.
